nfor those hierarchy-octant combinations for which this degeneracy is present.\nIf this degeneracy is absent, then only neutrino run gives a better result for\nfixed $\\theta_{13}$. However if we marginalize over $\\theta_{13}$ then,\nsensitivity corresponding to mixed run can be better than pure neutrino run.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 17 Sep 2014 16:14:50 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 2 Jan 2017 10:33:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-01-03"}
